column5: I got out last night for a little walleye fishing on the Sydenham river, just east of Wallaceburg!!  Caught this little guy on a rattlin bluefox spoon!!!    Tasted pretty good too!!    The ice was very sketchy, ranging anywhere from 1" - 4"  So if you go out, be very careful!!!
Very nice and congrats!  Just a warning, it will get very addictive!  Jeff
If I could get to the river right now, I would be there....lol
nice!  all of the essentials for a well balanced meal
Nice catch !!!!..well you are hooked for sure now...dinner looks great
Fantastic report - next time let us know what time dinner is

Excellent job!  That's an awesome picture.  Good thing you had your suit on.  Looks like it wouldn't have been such a bad idea to bring a stick and a puck along with you as well, the ice seems clean enough.
Hey, well done reelinrolly. Thats a nice fish, looks pretty tasty too, congrats.
I know the feeling of pulling your first walleye through the ice... it is awesome...  Congrats, The meal looks delicious.  Jen
great report!  nice catch.  I have heard the ice out that way is pretty thin.  godd to see you wearing the right clothing!  Cheers!
I think I will be giving it a shot today....with the cold weather the last few days it should of thickened everything up.......but Im sure not gonna take of the survival suit....lol
